title: unrecognised emulation mode: i386pep

labels.name: A-linkage
labels.description: Area: linking into static, shared libraries and binaries

body:
I get this issue on Windows when I try to compile a simple test file. This happens with the last few installers.

```
error: linking with `gcc` failed: exit code: 1
note: gcc '-m64' '-L' '\bin\rustlib\x86_64-w64-mingw32\lib' '-o' 'test.exe' 'test.o' '-Wl,--whole-archive' '-lmorestack' '-Wl,--no-whole-archive' '-fno-lto' '-fno-use-linker-plugin' '-Wl,--gc-sections' '-static-libgcc' '-Wl,--enable-long-section-names' '-Wl,--nxcompat' '\bin\rustlib\x86_64-w64-mingw32\lib\libnative-4e7c5e5c.rlib' '\bin\rustlib\x86_64-w64-mingw32\lib\libstd-4e7c5e5c.rlib' '\bin\rustlib\x86_64-w64-mingw32\lib\librand-4e7c5e5c.rlib' '\bin\rustlib\x86_64-w64-mingw32\lib\libsync-4e7c5e5c.rlib' '\bin\rustlib\x86_64-w64-mingw32\lib\librustrt-4e7c5e5c.rlib' '\bin\rustlib\x86_64-w64-mingw32\lib\libcollections-4e7c5e5c.rlib' '\bin\rustlib\x86_64-w64-mingw32\lib\libunicode-4e7c5e5c.rlib' '\bin\rustlib\x86_64-w64-mingw32\lib\liballoc-4e7c5e5c.rlib' '\bin\rustlib\x86_64-w64-mingw32\lib\liblibc-4e7c5e5c.rlib' '\bin\rustlib\x86_64-w64-mingw32\lib\libcore-4e7c5e5c.rlib' '-L' '\rust\.rust' '-L' '\rust' '-Wl,--whole-archive' '-Wl,-Bstatic' '-Wl,--no-whole-archive' '-Wl,-Bdynamic' '-lws2_32' '-lcompiler-rt'
note: /mingw-builds/x32-4.8.1-win32-dwarf-rev5/mingw32/bin/../lib/gcc/i686-w64-mingw32/4.8.1/../../../../i686-w64-mingw32/bin/ld.exe: unrecognised emulation mode: i386pep
Supported emulations: i386pe
collect2.exe: error: ld returned 1 exit status
```
